title: Weeping willow (Salix babylonica) branches, Mitchell Park, Milwaukee
description:
Weeping willow branches (Salix babylonica) on the bank of the Mitchell Park Lagoon in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.

It's also possible this is a white willow (Salix alba) or some related hybrid, but based on the relative lack of fine hair on the underside of the leaves (which gives Salix alba its white shade on the underside of the leaves) and the high level of weeping (pendulous) behavior of the branches, I think this is likely the weeping willow (Salix babylonica).
The Salix genus (the willows) are in the Malpighiales order (a very diverse plant order) and the Salicaceae family.

Photo taken early August 2023. Original key: IMG_6047
